  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Taijutsu (Strike)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 6</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 4</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 20 | <b>Successes:</b> 3</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 8 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 21</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> F, Mas, Mob</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>You make a melee attack against the target with your held weapon, suffering a -4 penalty to attack and damage rolls. You may take a 5 ft step before or after the attack. This can be done even if you've already moved this turn, and will not prevent you from moving normally this turn.<br><br>Once per round, if an opponent misses you with a melee attack, this technique can be used as an instant action to counter-attack. Doing so works as above, but the penalties are halves. This attack counts as an attack of opportunity (and so cannot be used if you have none remaining this round).<br><br>You cannot use both this technique and an avoid an attack or defensive maneuver technique in response to the same attack.</p>\n\n\n<p><b>Mastery:</b> The fifth step reduces the normal penalties to -2 (and thus, the instant action penalties to -1).</p>\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
